<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Other snippets on TMC - 9 Digital Tech Semester 2</title><link>https://tmcdigitech.github.io/dit9b/deepSpace/XXsnippets/</link><description>Recent content in Other snippets on TMC - 9 Digital Tech Semester 2</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-au</language><atom:link href="https://tmcdigitech.github.io/dit9b/deepSpace/XXsnippets/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Changing scenes</title><link>https://tmcdigitech.github.io/dit9b/deepSpace/XXsnippets/sceneChange/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tmcdigitech.github.io/dit9b/deepSpace/XXsnippets/sceneChange/</guid><description>&lt;p>At the top of any script which calls scene changes, you will need to add:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-cs" data-lang="cs">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">using&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nn">UnityEngine.SceneManagement&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>At the point in your script where you want to change scenes, add the line:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-cs" data-lang="cs">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="n">SceneManager&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="n">LoadScene&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="n">level&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">);&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>Replace &lt;code>level&lt;/code> either with the name of the scene (a string) or the number of the scene from &lt;em>File &amp;gt; Build Settings&lt;/em> (an int).&lt;/p>
